news.title: Madhya Pradesh okays new greenfield airport by acquiring 11,000 acres in Dewas
news.para: After its survey AAI found a location near Chapada-Hatpipliya tehsil of Dewas district as most suitable for meeting its technical criteria including topography, wind direction, connectivity, water bodies etc.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Land acquisition for Bhogapuram Airport to be completed soon
news.para: The government acquired about 2,150 acres of land so far and around 50 acres of land was yet to be acquired as the owners of the land approached the courts for more compensation.

news.title: Pune civic body to snap water connections over pending property tax post-Diwali
news.para: ​​Action will be taken against commercial establishments as first priority, after which residential properties will be targeted.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates phase-1 of Ahmedabad Metro rail project
news.para: With the inauguration, the 21-km corridor of the project between Thaltej and Vastral with 17 stations became operational.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for leasing out two land parcels worth Rs 29 crore at Katra
news.para: The reserve price for parcel 'A' having an area of 7,521.45 square metres is Rs 14.18 crore and for parcel 'B' with an area of 7,831.23 square meters, the price is Rs 14.97 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra government departments start receiving ULPIN data
news.para: Commonly called 'Aadhaar for land', the state has readied the Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN) for some 3crore documents - 2.62crore 7x12 extracts, and 70lakh property cards in the state.

news.title: Gujarat RERA suspends registration of Addor Aspire II
news.para: he notice was issued to the construction company, Addis Realtech LLP, in Navrangpura on September 23. The notice to Project Addor Aspire II has been issued under section 36 of RERA Act, 2016.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body collects Rs 6 crore property tax on last day of rebate
news.para: On Friday, the civic officials mopped up Rs 6 crore. However, the collection amount is going to rise as officials are yet to include the recovery done by the field staff and the online payment which continues till midnight.

news.title: Coimbatore: Court relieves residents' association from clutches of promoter
news.para: There are 126 individual villas in the retirement community - Soundarayam And Santhosham. It came into existence in 2006. The size of each villa ranged from 1,000 sq ft to 3,000 sq ft.

news.title: Kanpur development body freezes rates of flats under its various schemes
news.para: According to KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh KDA, it is an effort to give respite to citizens who are interested in having a flat in KDA schemes.

news.title: Vadodara civic body issues notices to Sanjaynagar residents
news.para: The notices have been issued to ensure that work on the housing scheme under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) can begin there.

news.title: Gurugram: Builder fined for felling tree without approval
news.para: The forest department on Friday issued a challan against a private builder for cutting a tree in DLF-2 area without the requisite permission from it. The move came after a resident complained about the tree felling to RWA, which subsequently reported it to the forest department.

news.title: Hyderabad: No takers for transferable development rights, owners fret & fume
news.para: Though the GHMC had issued Rs 3,500 crore worth TDR certificates to land losers, there are no takers despite property owners willing to sell their TDR at a discount of 67% of their value. Last year, some property owners sold their TDRs at 50% discount.

news.title: Delhi: MCD issues circular on prior intimation on transaction of properties by officials
news.para: ​As per the circular issued by the central establishment department of the MCD, any failure to abide by the provisions will be "viewed seriously and appropriate action shall be taken" in this regard.

news.title: Noida: Cameras at building sites, washing of roads when GRAP kicks in
news.para: In stage 1, CAQM has suggested dust mitigation, checking municipal, C&D and hazardous waste, water sprinkling and mechanised sweeping of roads, and use of anti-smoke guns at construction sites, among others.
